Dreading in the sense that I’m stressing out about doing well and keeping up, not in the sense that I’m not interested in the course itself
Sorry in advance for not having an answer for you, but if you don’t mind me asking how have you been prepping for 170? I’m also taking it next sem and am lowkey dreading it

^ Pretty much this

For 170 and 188, you either need to have an mind for the material, or just do a ton of practice (which takes a lot of dedication and time on top of the homework assignments). I haven't taken 184, but I think you really only need to put the time in on the projects to do well.

Easiest way imo is being able to give a lecture on any given topic in the course at any given moment. Teach your friends, your mom and your dog. Finish studying all the material in the first week, do all the exam problems in the second and then keep talking with TAs at every office hour.

Of course it's all a tradeoff. Unfortunately theres no easy way to get As other than just knowing the material and no one can say how long that'll take you. If you believe in yourself and need to do this, be absolute and spend your waking thoughts rigorously testing what you know and dont know and get good about getting deep into stuff you dont know.

history.content:
Hi, I'm putting together a schedule for my next five (or six) semesters and I'm double majoring in Math and CS. I want to take some graduate courses to fulfill some of my CS upper division units, but I need an A in the lower division versions. I don't know if an A- or B+ will be enough. I want to take 284B, 270 and 288. How difficult is it to get and A in CS 170, CS 184, and CS 188 (Not taken same semester)? Any advice? 

Note: Already started studying for CS 170, taking this next semester.
history.subject: Get an A in CS 170, CS 184, and CS 188
